added.description: Mayor Foghorn Leghorn hires The Looney Builders to build a giant water slide for Looneyburg's waterpark. He keeps adding onto the design with the support of Bugs until problems arise.

added.title: Ice Creamed
added.description: It's Taz's birthday, so The Looney Builders build him a huge ice cream sundae. Porky worries about making a mistake and delays the build causing the ice cream to start to melt.

added.title: Tweety-Go-Round
added.description: Tweety leads The Looney Builders in building a new merry-go-round at the park for the kids. His crane breaks down and his small size affects his ability to contribute to the build.

added.title: Smash House
added.description: The Looney Builders learn that Taz accidentally destroyed his house, so they set out to build him a new one that's smash-proof.

added.title: Play Day
added.description: When the Looney Builders build themselves a playground, Daffy gets so excited about his section that he takes all the supplies for himself.

added.title: Rock On
added.description: The Looney Builders are hired by Mac and Tosh Gopher to build them a home underground. Daffy can't remove rocks from the area fast enough and fails to ask for help.

added.title: Buzz In
added.description: Bizzy Buzzard's mom hires The Looney Builders to build her family a new nest. Bizzy wants to help but keeps getting in the way creating all sorts of problems for the crew.

added.title: Stories
added.description: The Looney Builders are hired by Hoots Talon to expand and paint the old library. They enlist master painter Sylvester who faces his fear of heights with his build buddy, Tweety.

added.title: Cheesy Peasy
added.description: The Looney Builders are hired by the Mouse Sisters to build a bridge over a mac and cheese spill. Lola turns the job into a game which results in the crew losing sight of the bigger goal.

added.title: Looney Science
added.description: The Looney Builders build a science museum in the desert where Wile E. Coyote becomes distracted by the Road Runner.

added.title: Big Feet
added.description: Mayor Leghorn hires The Looney Builders to build a water wheel in the forest where Porky worries about a mythical creature named "Big Feet."

added.title: Squirreled Away
added.description: The Looney Builders build Tibs Squirrel a closet in his tree, but it won't fit all of Tibs' stuff and he doesn't want to get rid of anything.

added.title: Beach Battle
added.description: When The Looney Builders enter a sandcastle building contest, Tweety sees the competition and loses confidence in his idea.

added.title: Game Time
added.description: Chef Hector hires The Looney Builders to build him a burger restaurant, but Daffy is so focused on beating his handheld game that he causes major setbacks.

added.title: Soup Up
added.description: As The Looney Builders help Petunia build a greenhouse, she can't wait for the veggies to grow and does everything she can to speed up the process.

added.title: Blast Off
added.description: When Marvin the Martian crash lands in Looneyburg, he's in a hurry to leave and hires The Looney Builders to build him a spaceship.

added.title: K-9: Space Puppy
added.description: Marvin the Martian hires The Looney Builders to build a doghouse on Mars for his puppy, K-9. Daffy soon bonds with K-9 and comes up with a plan to prolong their playtime.

added.title: Cousin Billy
added.description: When Daffy's cool cousin Billy hires The Looney Builders to build her an art studio, Daffy tries to show off to prove how cool he is.

added.title: Cheddar Days
added.description: The Mouse Sisters hire The Looney Builders to build a cheese café featuring a mural by Sylvester who is having a bad day.

added.title: Taz Recycle
added.description: When The Looney Builders build Taz a wrecking ball vehicle, he struggles to learn how to operate it.

added.title: Sea School
added.description: The Looney Builders face underwater challenges as they build a sea school for Moxie Manatee.

added.title: Underwater Star
added.description: Moxie Manatee hires The Looney Builders to build an obstacle course for the Sandy Shells Preschool Games, but Lola isn't listening to her crew.

added.title: Party Boat
added.description: The Looney Builders build a party boat for Mac and Tosh when Tweety accidentally makes a mistake but doesn't ask for help.

added.title: Mail Whale
added.description: The Looney Builders try to help Winston Whale by building him a mail truck, but Winston is used to working alone.

added.title: Skate Park
added.description: The Looney Builders build a skate park for the kids, but it soon interferes with Hoots Talon and his friends' activities.

added.title: Batty Kathy
added.description: As The Looney Builders build Kathy Bat an upside-down radio station, Porky has concerns but doesn't speak up.

added.title: Honey Bunny
added.description: Queen Beatrice hires The Looney Builders to build a workshop in her beehive where there is one rule the crew has trouble following.

added.title: Castle Hassle
added.description: Prince Lionel of England hires The Looney Builders to build him a party room for his birthday, then proceeds to boss the crew around.

added.title: Catwalk
added.description: The Looney Builders are hired by Penelope Pussycat to build a fashion runway in France where they are encouraged to make their design bigger and more fun.

added.title: Dim Sum
added.description: Chef Poyung Panda hires The Looney Builders to build her a Dim Sum bus in China. The crew faces a major setback and Bugs worries about letting down his favorite chef.

added.title: Crane Game
added.description: As The Looney Builders build a giant claw game for Chibi Critter's arcade in Japan, they discover the claw part is broken.

added.title: Speedy
added.description: The Looney Builders rush to build a soccer stadium in Mexico for their fast customer, Speedy Gonzalez.
